	   <tr><td colspan=2>yes, he is excceedingly tough. <br>First off he heals himself constantly (luckily he can be interrupted ) - SHeal I would say ( thank Tunare it is not CHeal).<br><br>Second, when armed with the Sword (visible), he keeps dispelling himself, usually getting rid of dots, slws debuffs, etc... (Seems to be the one main reason for the sword's proc, IMHO)<br><br>Third he hits for 250+, double and triple strikes (on a paladin with Ac 1070 unbuffed, level 55 ).<br><br>Fourth, he is hard to pull single, often bringing the staff sergeant along ( who is tough himself ).<br><br>Fifth, he seems to be extremly p****d off when debuffed ( we noticed with the Druids Ro'series of spells - "sunder" once, be summoned...8/ ), usually resultig in being summoned ( which means a quite sudden death....)<br><br>Killed him twice today, first time our group had to break off, med up and reenter kael ( pal 55, mage 60, Ranger 60, cleric 57 druid 52 druid 54 ) to slay him (after rezzing the druids ) to slay him on the second run - as for tactics, on the second run we filled his buff-box with root and dots, before casting snares, slows and other debuffs, and had the melees (tanks and pet) fight<br>him down to 1/3rd, the nuked him away with starfires. Paladin and cleric tried to stun as often as possible ( which helped interrupt casting). Second time, two full groups (all 52nd to 55th, one bard of 40th) took him down in an all out slugfest ( no sword then ), with two&nbsp;&nbsp;casualties (one tank, one druid).<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
